{{Quote|You're about to face off with the dark troopers. You had your hands full with one. Let's see how well you do against a platoon.|Gideon|<ref name="Chapter 16" />}}
'''Dark Troopers''' were experimental soldiers<ref name="Commander" /> created as part of the [[Galactic Empire]]'s [[Dark Trooper project|dark trooper program]].<ref name="Dawn" /> Dark trooper models were body suits worn by a [[human]] [[pilot]]. Nevertheless, Dark Troopers also<ref name="Chapter 16">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 16: The Rescue}}</ref> resembled the [[DT-series sentry droid]]s also used by the Empire.<ref name="The Wynkahthu Job">{{Rebels|The Wynkahthu Job}}</ref> Eventually, research indicated that the human pilot was the final weakness to be removed, heralding in the [[Phase-III Dark Trooper]] as a battle droid. However, an entire [[platoon]] of these Dark Trooper droids were destroyed by [[Jedi Knight]] [[Luke Skywalker]]<ref name="Chapter 16" /> in [[9 ABY]].<ref name="Date">{{MandoDate|16}}</ref> [[Moff]] [[Gideon]] then returned the Dark Trooper project to its suit-focus and created the [[Dark Trooper phase 4|phase four suit]] with [[beskar]] alloy.<ref name="Chapter 23">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 23: The Spies}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|Thanks to your planet's rich resources, I have created the next generation Dark Trooper suit forged from beskar alloy.|Moff Gideon|<ref name="Chapter 23" />}}
[[File:TatooineGarrison-Commander.png|thumb|left|250px|Second-generation Dark Troopers served alongside various Imperial forces in the Battle for Tatooine.]]
[[Phase II Dark Trooper]]s were deployed for evaluation by the [[Imperial Military]] during the [[Galactic Civil War]] and were utilized in the [[Battle for Tatooine]].<ref name="Commander" /> By the time of the [[Phase-III Dark Trooper|third-generation dark trooper]] used in [[Moff]] [[Gideon]]'s [[Gideon's Imperial remnant|Imperial remnant]]<ref name="Chapter 16" /> in the [[Standard year|year]] [[9 ABY]],<ref name="Date" /> it was decided the human pilot was the last weakness in the dark trooper design, transforming the third generation units into [[battle droid]]s.<ref name="Chapter 16" />

The third generation units<ref name="Chapter 16" /> were deployed on [[Tython]] to retrieve [[Din Grogu|Grogu]] after he was brought to the [[seeing stone]]. These dark troopers were equipped with jet boosters in their feet to enable in-atmospheric flight and were capable of launching directly from a cruiser, as opposed to having to be deployed in a troop transport.<ref name="Chapter 14">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 14: The Tragedy}}</ref> Later, when the [[Mandalorian]] [[bounty hunter]] [[Din Djarin]] and his allies [[Second rescue of Grogu|attempted to rescue]] Grogu from [[Gideon's light cruiser]], he activated his [[Gideon's Dark Trooper platoon|dark trooper platoon]], though it was eliminated by [[Jedi Master]] [[Luke Skywalker]].<ref name="Chapter 16" />

[[File:ImperialDarkTroopers-SWL2024update.png|thumb|right|300px|Third-generation Dark Troopers in action]]
Sometime later, Gideon changed the Dark Trooper from a droid into a [[Dark Trooper phase 4|battle armor]] worn by himself and his new clone army after his [[Imperial armored commando]]<nowiki/>s [[Extraction of Moff Gideon|rescued]] him from the [[New Republic]]. The armor had a similar style to [[Mandalorian armor]], and was built with [[beskar]] alloy. It was also equipped with a [[helmet]] and [[jetpack]]. Similar to a Mandalorian armor, it had a [[Ka'rta]] on the chest plate of the armor.<ref name="Chapter 23" />

{{Droid-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Operative, I have apportioned some experimental ''Dark Troopers'' to Tatooine for evaluation. I have dispatched them to you for this operation. Do not fail the Empire.|[[Kosh]] in ''Star Wars: Commander's'' Imperial campaign|<ref name="Commander" />}}
Dark Troopers were first introduced in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity in the [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Dark Forces]]''. The [[canon]] version seen in ''[[Star Wars: Commander]]'', resembles the [[purge trooper]] seen in ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]''.

The DT-series sentry droid was based on the dark trooper designs.<ref name="Wynkahthu Recon">{{RebelsRecon|UqxnQZDRF4g|#3.08: Inside "The Wynkahthu Job" &#124; Star Wars Rebels|sw_url=video/rebels-recon-inside-the-wynkahthu-job}}</ref>

''[[Dawn of Rebellion]]'' introduced the dark trooper program as an effort to create Imperial battle droids that ended as a debacle, thereby contributing to the [[Joint Chiefs of the Imperial Military|Joint Chiefs]] becoming disenchanted with combat droids.<ref name="Dawn" /> This matches the program's depiction in [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]], where the [[Phase I Dark Trooper|Phase I dark trooper]] and [[Phase II Dark Trooper/Legends|Phase II dark troopers]] were battle droid models.<ref name="Dark Forces">''[[Star Wars: Dark Forces]]''</ref> However, "[[Chapter 16: The Rescue]]" suggested the dark trooper program in canon had only recently taken a turn towards fully droid soldiers, with prior Dark Troopers being referenced as armored suits.<ref name="Chapter 16" /> ''[[Star Wars: Character Encyclopedia, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''<ref name="SWCEUAE">''[[Star Wars: Character Encyclopedia, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> and the "Scene to Stats" article on the Dark Troopers on [[Atomic Mass Games]]'s website later affirmed that the dark trooper program started as a combat suit effort, before later shifting into droids, in canon.<ref name="Scene to Stats Dark Troopers">{{AtomicMassGames|url=transmission/scene-to-stat-dark-troopers|text=Scene to Stats: Dark Troopers|date=2023-01-10}}</ref>

